Wash and dry all produce. Preheat #oven to 450 degrees. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch wedges (like steak fries). Cut @Lemon{1} into wedges. Mince or grate @Garlic{2%clove}. Finely chop @Parsley{¼%ounce}. Drain @Artichokes{1%jar}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%tablespoon} and a large pinch of @Salt{pinch} and @Pepper{pinch}. Bake until golden brown and crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}, turning once halfway through.

Drain and finely chop @Capers{1%ounce}. In a #small bowl{}, combine @Mayonnaise{1%jar}, parsley, capers, garlic (to taste), and a squeeze of lemon. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Cook the fish: Season @Rockfish{12%ounce} on all sides with salt and pepper. With 5-7 minutes to go on the potatoes, heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #large pan{} over high heat. Once very hot (oil should shimmer), add rockfish. Cook until slightly golden on outside and just opaque on inside, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

Toss @Arugula{2%ounce} and artichokes in a #large bowl{} with a squeeze of lemon, drizzle of olive oil, and pinch of salt and pepper.

Finish: Plate the seared rockfish alongside the arugula artichoke salad and oven fries. Serve with a dollop of caper aioli and a lemon wedge. Enjoy!